@startuml evolution_symbiosis
skinparam monochrome true

title Simbiosi multi-agente e signaling feromonico

box "Distributed Node - RPi / ESP32 / STM32 (Node A)" #LightGreen
  participant "Agente A\n(Specialista)" as A
end box

box "Edge Node - Linux Gateway" #LightYellow
  participant "MQTT Broker" as MQTT
end box

box "Distributed Node - RPi / ESP32 / STM32 (Node B)" #PaleGreen
  participant "Agente B\n(Sottoscritto alla nicchia)" as B
end box

box "Cloud/Hub - Linux Server" #LightBlue
  participant "Fitness Evaluator" as FE
end box

== Rilevamento pattern e segnale feromonico ==

A -> A : detect_pattern(high_volatility)
A -> MQTT : publish("tr4d3rz/ecosystem/signal/{agent_id}", CBOR_Pheromone_Signal)
note right of A
  **Hosted on:** Distributed Node - RPi / ESP32 / STM32
  **Topic logico di nicchia:** high-volatility
  **Topic MQTT canonico:** tr4d3rz/ecosystem/signal/{agent_id}
  **Payload (CBOR map):**
  {
    "v": 1,
    "ts": uint64,
    "node": node_id,
    "type": "ecosystem.signal.pheromone",
    "agent_id": UUID,
    "niche_id": "high-volatility",
    "strength": float32,  // 0.0..1.0
    "regime_type": text
  }
end note

MQTT -> B : forward pheromone signal
note left of B
  **Hosted on:** Distributed Node - RPi / ESP32 / STM32
  B subscribes to cooperative signal streams
  and filters payload.niche_id == "high-volatility".
end note

B -> B : integrate strength and regime_type\nas extra FSM input
B -> MQTT : publish("tr4d3rz/ecosystem/signal/{agent_id}", CBOR_Response_Signal)
note left of B
  Response payload keeps the same CBOR schema
  and may lower or reinforce strength.
end note

MQTT -> A : deliver response signal
A -> FE : report cooperation_gain
B -> FE : report cooperation_gain
FE -> MQTT : publish("tr4d3rz/ecosystem/fitness/{agent_id}", CBOR_Fitness_Update)

footer Hosting: Distributed RPi/ESP32/STM32 -> Agents A/B and pheromone FSM inputs; Edge Linux Gateway -> MQTT Broker; Cloud/Hub Linux Server -> Fitness Evaluator | MQTT Topics: tr4d3rz/ecosystem/signal/{agent_id}, tr4d3rz/ecosystem/fitness/{agent_id} | CBOR Payload: v, ts, node, type, agent_id, niche_id, strength(0.0-1.0), regime_type
@enduml
